INSTALL
=======

1. Copy *.class.inc to the drupal includes directory
   (cp *.class.inc /your/drupal/dir/includes/)
   Snoopy.class.inc is optional
2. Install the mysql file
   (mysql --user=user -ppassword database <amazon.mysql)
3. Copy the amazon.module to the modules directory
   (cp amazon.module /your/drupal/dir/modules/)
4. In the adminstration section go to site configuration, them click
   modules and enable the amazon module
5. then go to the Amazon administration subsection, fill in your developer
   key, affiliate ID, and select the modes and you're done.  
6. you should select a type of search for the startup page 
   (module.php?mod=amazon) in the admin section
